    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies. This driver-spec example features the Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock for optimal power delivery. Critical preventive maintenance has been performed, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement to maintain structural integrity under lateral load. The suspension geometry remains precise with upgraded bushings, and the throttle mapping provides the linear response purists demand. While the exterior displays minor road-going patina consistent with its 'good' status, the internal mechanical synchronization and compression across all cylinders remain robust. An excellent candidate for an enthusiast seeking a tactile, analog performance platform.",
